column9: Description
str
USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/record<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Opens and closes the Duty Recorder interface.

USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/recordready [subcommand]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Opens and closes the Duty Recorder interface.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Subcommands:<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>[countdowntime]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Initiate a record ready check<hex:02100103>　　to begin recording a duty.<hex:02100103>　　When all party members<hex:02100103>　　consent to the recording,<hex:02100103>　　a countdown will start at<hex:02100103>　　the specified time.<hex:02100103>　　Subsequent uses of this<hex:02100103>　　command during the same<hex:02100103>　　duty will function as both a<hex:02100103>　　ready check and countdown.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>Opens the Duty Recorder interface when no subcommand is specified.
USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/pvpteamcmd<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Opens and closes the PvP team menu.
USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/saddlebag<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Opens and closes your chocobo saddlebag.
USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/magiaright<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Spins your magia board clockwise.
USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/magialeft<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Spins your magia board counterclockwise.
ALIASES:<hex:02100103>　/cwlinkshellcmd, /cwlcmd<hex:02100103>USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/cwlinkshellcmd<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Opens and closes the Cross-world Linkshell window.

ALIASES:<hex:02100103>　/quickchat, /qchat<hex:02100103>USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/quickchat [quick chat message]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Sends a Quick Chat message. Can only be used during Crystalline Conflict.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Example:<hex:02100103>　/quickchat Charge <t><hex:02100103>　(Sends the Quick Chat message<hex:02100103>　"Charge" using a specified<hex:02100103>　target.)

USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/bluespellbook [subcommand]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Open and register active actions in the Blue Magic Spellbook.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Subcommands:<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>set "blue mage action" on<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Adds the specified blue<hex:02100103>　　mage action to the list<hex:02100103>　　of active actions in the<hex:02100103>　　current set.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03> set "blue mage action" off<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Removes the specified blue<hex:02100103>　　mage action from the list of<hex:02100103>　　active actions in the current<hex:02100103>　　set.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>preset [active set 1-5]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Load the specified set of<hex:02100103>　　active actions.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>clear<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Remove all active actions<hex:02100103>　　from the current active<hex:02100103>　　action set.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>Opens the Blue Magic Spellbook when no subcommand is specified.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Examples:<hex:02100103>　/bluespellbook set “Water Cannon”<hex:02100103>　(Sets the blue mage action<hex:02100103>　Water Cannon as an active<hex:02100103>　action in the current set.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>　/bluespellbook preset 2<hex:02100103>　(Loads active set 2.)

USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/magiaattack [placeholder]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Spin the magia board to match the elemental weakness of the specified target. If no target is specified, matches based on current target.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Common Placeholders:<hex:02100103>　<t>, <target>, <1>-<8><hex:02100103><hex:02100103>A full list of placeholders can be found on the Lodestone Play Guide.

USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/magiadefense [placeholder]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Spin the magia board to match the elemental affinity of the specified target. If no target is specified, matches based on current target.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Common Placeholders:<hex:02100103>　<t>, <target>, <1>-<8><hex:02100103><hex:02100103>A full list of placeholders can be found on the Lodestone Play Guide.

USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/magiaauto [subcommand]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Set the magia board to automatically spin based on your current target.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Subcommands:<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>attack (atk)<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Automatically spin the magia<hex:02100103>　　board to match the elemental<hex:02100103>　　weakness of current target.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>defense (def)<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Automatically spin the magia<hex:02100103>　　board to match the elemental<hex:02100103>　　affinity of current target.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>off <hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Disable automatic spinning.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>Toggle between attack, defense, and off when no subcommand is specified.

ALIASES:<hex:02100103>　/cwlinkshell1, /cwl1<hex:02100103>USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/cwlinkshell1 [message]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Sends a message to all members of the cross-world linkshell you have registered in cross-world linkshell slot 1, regardless of their location. Typing /cwlinkshell1 or /cwl1 without a message switches the default chat mode to [Cross-world Linkshell 1].

Typing /cwlinkshell6 or /cwl6 without a message switches the default chat mode to [Cross-world Linkshell 6].

Typing /cwlinkshell8 or /cwl8 without a message switches the default chat mode to [Cross-world Linkshell 8].

ALIASES:<hex:02100103>　/graphicpresets, /gpresets<hex:02100103>USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/graphicpresets [preset<hex:02100103>　number]<hex:02100103>→Load one of several preset graphics configuration settings.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Preset Configurations:<hex:02100103><hex:0208F201D5E4E94F04FFF0E4>　　1: Standard (Mac)<hex:02100103>　　2: Middle  (Mac)<hex:02100103>　　3: High (Mac)<hex:02100103>　　4: Extra-High (Mac)<hex:02100103>　　5: Maximum (Mac)<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Example:<hex:02100103>　　/graphicpresets 2<hex:02100103>　　=Sets graphics settings to<hex:02100103> 　　preset 2.<hex:FFF0E7>　　1: Standard (Laptop)<hex:02100103>　　2: Standard (Desktop)<hex:02100103>　　3: High (Laptop)<hex:02100103>　　4: High (Desktop)<hex:02100103>　　5: Maximum<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Example:<hex:02100103>　　/graphicpresets 2<hex:02100103>　　(Sets graphics settings to<hex:02100103>　　preset 2.)<hex:03>
ALIASES:<hex:02100103>　/fellowship, /fs<hex:02100103>USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/fellowship<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Opens and closes the Fellowship interface.
ALIASES:<hex:02100103>　/fellowshipfinder, /fsfinder<hex:02100103>USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/fellowshipfinder<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Opens and closes the Fellowship Finder interface.
ALIASES:<hex:02100103>　/collection, /coll<hex:02100103>USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/collection<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Opens and closes the Collection interface.
ALIASES:<hex:02100103>　/newgame+, /ng+<hex:02100103>USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/newgame+<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Opens the New Game+ interface.

USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/dice [chat mode] [subcommand]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Displays a random number between 0 and 999 in the specified chat channel. Displays in the current chat mode when no chat mode is specified.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Chat Modes:<hex:02100103>　Party<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>party<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103>, <hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>p<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　Alliance<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>alliance<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103>, <hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>al<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　Free Company<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>freecompany<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103>, <hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>fc<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　PvP Team<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>pvpteam<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103>, <hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>pt<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　Linkshell<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>linkshell1-8<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103>, <hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>l1-8<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　Cross-world Linkshell<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>cwlinkshell1-8<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103>, <hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>cwl1-8<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Subcommands:<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>[upper limit]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set an upper limit to display a random number between 1 and the specified number. Displays a random number between 0 and 999 when no upper limit is specified.<hex:02100103>　　Upper limit range: 2-999<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Examples:<hex:02100103>　/dice<hex:02100103>　(Displays a random number<hex:02100103>　in the current chat mode.)<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>　/dice 16<hex:02100103>　(Displays a random number<hex:02100103>　between 1 and 16 in the<hex:02100103>　current chat mode.)<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>　/dice cwl1<hex:02100103>　(Displays a random number<hex:02100103>　in the Cross-world Linkshell 1<hex:02100103>　channel.)<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>　/dice cwl1 16<hex:02100103>　(Displays a random number<hex:02100103>　between 1 and 16 in the<hex:02100103>　Cross-world Linkshell 1<hex:02100103>　channel.)

USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/nameplatetype [category] [setting number]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Change PC display type settings.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Category:<hex:02100103>　All Players<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>all<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　Your Character<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>self<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　Party Members<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>party<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　Other PCs<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>other<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　Friends<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>friend<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　Crystalline Conflict Opponents<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>feast<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Setting Number<hex:02100103>　1: Full Name<hex:02100103>　2: Surname Abbreviated<hex:02100103>　3: Forename Abbreviated<hex:02100103>　4: Initials<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Example:<hex:02100103>　/nameplatetype all 4<hex:02100103>　(Set display names to<hex:02100103>　initials for all players.)

USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/nameplatedisp [category] [setting number]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Change PC display name settings.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Category:<hex:02100103>　All Players<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>all<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　Your Character<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>self<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　Party Members<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>party<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　Other PCs<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>other<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　Friends<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>friend<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　Crystalline Conflict Opponents<hex:02100103>　　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>feast<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Setting Number<hex:02100103>　1: Always<hex:02100103>　2: During Battle<hex:02100103>　3: When Targeted<hex:02100103>　4: Never<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Example:<hex:02100103>　/nameplatedisp all 4<hex:02100103>　(Set display names to never<hex:02100103>　display for all players.)

USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/fashion [accessory]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Equip a specified fashion accessory.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Example:<hex:02100103>　/fashion “parasol”<hex:02100103>　(Equip the parasol accessory.)
USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/fashionguide<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Opens and closes the Fashion Accessories interface.
ALIASES:<hex:02100103>　/officialsite, /site<hex:02100103>USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/officialsite<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Opens and closes the Official Sites interface.
//setGearset<hex:02100103>リアルイベント用コマンド。<hex:02100103>アーマリーチェスト内のアイテムをもとに、自動的にバトルジョブのギアセットを生成する。

ALIASES:<hex:02100103>　/petglamour, /petglam, /egiglamour<hex:02100103>USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/petglamour [summon] [glamour]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Alter the appearance of select summons. You must resummon the egi for the glamour to take effect. Command not applicable in PvP instances.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Summon Name:<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>Carbuncle<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>Garuda-Egi<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>Titan-Egi<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>Ifrit-Egi<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>Eos<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Glamour:<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>Carbuncle<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>Emerald Carbuncle<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>Topaz Carbuncle<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>Ruby Carbuncle<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>Garuda-Egi<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>Titan-Egi<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>Ifrit-Egi<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>Selene<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103><hex:02100103>The glamour will be removed when no glamour is specified.<hex:02100103>Displays pet glamour settings in chat log when no subcommand is specified.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Example:<hex:02100103>　/petglamour "Garuda-Egi" "Ruby Carbuncle"<hex:02100103>　(Garuda-Egi will appear glamoured as Ruby Carbuncle.)<hex:02100103>　/petglamour "Garuda-Egi"<hex:02100103>　(Returns Garuda-Egi to default appearance.)<hex:02100103>　/petglamour<hex:02100103>　(Displays pet glamour settings.)

USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/petsize [summon] [size]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Alter the size of select summons. Command not applicable in PvP instances. These settings will not apply to other players.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Egi Name:<hex:02100103>　Demi-Bahamut<hex:02100103>　Demi-Phoenix<hex:02100103>　Ruby Ifrit<hex:02100103>　Topaz Titan<hex:02100103>　Emerald Garuda<hex:02100103>　Solar Bahamut<hex:02100103>　all<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Size:<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>large<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set summon size to large.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>medium<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set summon size to medium.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>small<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set summon size to small.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>Toggles between small, medium, and large when no size is specified. Returns an error when attempting to toggle using “all.”<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Example:<hex:02100103>　/petsize "Ruby Ifrit" "small"<hex:02100103>　(Set Ruby Ifrit's size to small.)

USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/ridepillion [placeholder] [subcommand]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Ride pillion on a selected party member's mount.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Subcommands:<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>[seat number]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Select your desired seat on the mount.<hex:02100103>　　Available options: 1-7<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Common Placeholders:<hex:02100103>　<t>, <target>, <1>-<8><hex:02100103><hex:02100103>If the desired seat is already selected, you will be placed in the next available seat. Seat 1 will be selected if unspecified.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Example:<hex:02100103>　/ridepillion <2> 1<hex:02100103>　(Ride in seat 1 of party member 2.)
USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/patchnote<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Opens the Patch Notes page on the official site.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>Launches using your default browser.
USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/portrait<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Opens and closes the Portraits interface.
ALIASES:<hex:02100103>　/adventurerplate, /myplate<hex:02100103>USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/myplate<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Opens and closes your adventurer plate.

ALIASES:<hex:02100103>　/tell, /t<hex:02100103>USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/tell [PC name]@[World name] [message]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Sends a message to a specific PC on a specified World. Typing /tell or /t [PC name]@[World name] without a message switches the default chat mode to [Tell].<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Example:<hex:02100103>　/tell [PC name]@Bahamut Hello<hex:02100103>　(Sends the message "Hello" to<hex:02100103>　[PC name] on the World<hex:02100103>　Bahamut.)

USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/alarm "name" [clock type] [repeat] [time] [reminder] [sound effect] [mute]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Set an alarm for a specified time using local, server, or Eorzea time.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Clock Type:<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>lt<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the alarm using local time.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>st<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the alarm using server<hex:02100103>　　time.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>et<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the alarm using Eorzea<hex:02100103>　　time.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Repeat:<hex:02100103>　Use "repeat" or "rp" to set an<hex:02100103>　hourly alarm.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Time:<hex:02100103>　Times must be set using the 24-<hex:02100103>　hour clock.<hex:02100103>　Time values: 0000-2400<hex:02100103>　The hour must be omitted<hex:02100103>　when using the repeat<hex:02100103>　subcommand.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Reminder:<hex:02100103>　A notification can be given up<hex:02100103>　to 60 minutes prior to the<hex:02100103>　alarm.<hex:02100103>　Time values: 0-60<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Sound Effect:<hex:02100103>　Play a designated sound effect.<hex:02100103>　Sound effect values: 00-05<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Mute:<hex:02100103>　Mute sound effects while<hex:02100103>　undertaking duties.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>The repeat, reminder, sound effect, and mute subcommands can be omitted.<hex:02100103>The "clear" subcommand can be used to delete all alarms.<hex:02100103>Opens the alarm interface when no subcommands are specified.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Examples:<hex:02100103>　/alarm Raid lt 2000 10 se04<hex:02100103>　(Sets the "Raid" alarm for<hex:02100103>　20:00 local time, with a<hex:02100103>　notification given 10<hex:02100103>　minutes prior.)<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>　/alarm Party lt rp 30 se05<hex:02100103>　(Sets the "Party" alarm as<hex:02100103>　an hourly alarm, 30 minutes<hex:02100103>　past the hour in local time.)

If no placeholder is specified, then you will enter ground targeting mode.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Common Placeholders:<hex:02100103>　<t>, <target>, <1>-<8>, gtoff<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>A full list of placeholders can be found on the Lodestone Play Guide.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Example:<hex:02100103>　/blueaction “Water Cannon” <t><hex:02100103>　(Executes Water Cannon on<hex:02100103>　the specified target.)

USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/hotbar [subcommand]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Edit and configure hotbar settings. Only available in PvE areas.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Subcommands<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>action "action name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified action to slot [#2] in hotbar page [#1]. If "current" is entered for [#1], then the action will be set in the page displayed in hotbar 1. If [#2] is omitted, the action will be set to the lowest-numbered slot available. If both [#1] and [#2] are omitted, the action will be set to the lowest-numbered slot available on the lowest-numbered hotbar available. This applies to all of the following subcommands.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>blueaction "blue mage action name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified general action to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>item "item name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified item to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>emote "emote name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified companion action to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>pet "action name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified pet action to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>minion "minion name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified minion to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>mount "mount name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified mount to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>enemysign "enemy sign name" [#1] [number]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Replace current hotbar with hotbar [number].  If "next" or "prev" is entered in [number], then you can scroll through the pages of hotbar 1.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>copy [class 1] [#1] [class 2] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Copy the contents of [class 1] hotbar [#1] to the [class 2] hotbar [#2].<hex:02100103>　　The subcommand "current" can be used to specify your current class.<hex:02100103>　　The subcommand "share" can be used instead of a class to specify your shared hotbar.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>display [number] on<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Display hotbar [number].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>display [number] off<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Hide hotbar [number].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>display [number]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Toggle on/off hotbar [number].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>share [number] on<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Make hotbar [number] shared.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>share [number] off<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Unshare hotbar [number] and assign it to your current class/job.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>share [number]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Toggle between on/off.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>remove [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Remove the action assigned to slot [#2] on hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　　Replace [#2] with "all" to remove all actions from hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Examples:<hex:02100103>　/hotbar action "Mount<hex:02100103>　Roulette" 1 1<hex:02100103>　(Places Mount Roulette in<hex:02100103>　slot [#1] on hotbar [#1].)<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>　/hotbar change 2<hex:02100103>　(Replaces hotbar [#1] with<hex:02100103>　hotbar [#2].)

USAGE:<hex:02100103>　/pvphotbar [subcommand]<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>→Edit and configure hotbar settings. This command can only be used with the PvP hotbar.<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Subcommands<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>action "action name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified PvP action to slot [#2] in hotbar page [#1]. If "current" is entered for [#1], then the action will be set in the page displayed in hotbar 1. If [#2] is omitted, the action will be set to the lowest-numbered slot available. If both [#1] and [#2] are omitted, the action will be set to the lowest-numbered slot available on the lowest-numbered hotbar available. This applies to all of the following subcommands.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>general "general action name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified general action to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>item "item name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified item to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>emote "emote name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified emote to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>companion "companion action name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified companion action to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>pet "action name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified pet action to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>minion "minion name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified minion to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>mount "mount name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified mount to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>enemysign "enemy sign name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified enemy sign to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>waymark "waymark name" [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Set the specified waymark to slot [#2] in hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>change [number]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Replace current hotbar with hotbar [number].  If "next" or "prev" is entered in [number], then you can scroll through the pages of hotbar 1.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>copy [job 1] [#1] [job 2] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Copy the contents of [job 1] hotbar [#1] to the [job 2] hotbar [#2].<hex:02100103>　　The subcommand "current" can be used to specify your current job.<hex:02100103>　　The subcommand "share" can be used instead of a job to specify your shared hotbar.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>display [number] on<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Display hotbar [number].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>display [number] off<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Hide hotbar [number].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>display [number]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Toggle on/off hotbar [number].<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>share [number] on<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Make hotbar [number] shared.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>share [number] off<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Unshare hotbar [number] and assign it to your current job.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>share [number]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Toggle between on/off.<hex:02100103>　<hex:024804F201FA03><hex:024904F201FB03>remove [#1] [#2]<hex:0249020103><hex:0248020103><hex:02100103>　　Remove the action assigned to slot [#2] on hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103>　　Replace [#2] with "all" to remove all actions from hotbar [#1].<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>>>Examples:<hex:02100103>　/pvphotbar action "Purify" 1 1<hex:02100103>　(Places Purify in slot [#1]<hex:02100103>　on hotbar [#1].)<hex:02100103><hex:02100103>　/pvphotbar change 2<hex:02100103>　(Replaces PvP hotbar [#1]<hex:02100103>　with PvP hotbar [#2].)
